<html>
    <head>
        <title>Hello, World</title>
		<link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="{{contextRoot}}/css/styles.css">
    </head>
    <body>
    	<div id="summary">
    		<br/>
    		<strong>Hello World Sample</strong>
	    	<p>
	    		This sample demonstrates using DTL variables and filters. The context handler sets the value of the helloWorld
	    		variable to an HTML tag setting the value bold. The use of the 'safe' filter ensures that the contents of 
	    		the helloWorld variable is not escaped.  
	    	</p>
    		<br/>
    		<strong>Source</strong>
	    	<p>
	    	<ul>
	    	<li><a href="showsource?sourcePath=helloworld.dtl">resources/helloworld.dtl</a> - The template file</li>
	    	<li><a href="showsource?sourcePath=handlers/HelloWorldContext.js">resources/handlers/HelloWorldContext.js</a> - The Context that loads the helloWorld variable</li>
	    	</ul>
	    	</p>
	    </div>
	    <hr style="color: #f00; background-color: #f00; height: 2px;">
	    <br/>
    	{{ helloWorld|safe }}
    </body>
</html>
